      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a bad sprain, you need to be more aggressive than just ice and elevation. You should immediately start taking a high-dose anti-inflammatory, like an NSAID, and try a combination of compression and elevation, but I'm going to push you to try a specialized sports massage or a high-grade physical therapy session right away. If you really want to try at home, take two full days of aggressive icing, and then start taking a full dose of Ibuprofen every six hours.",
